# Deploying to Cloudflare Workers (static assets)

This site is a Next.js static export (`output: 'export'` in `next.config.ts`) served as [Workers static assets](https://developers.cloudflare.com/workers/static-assets/) — never Pages (maintenance mode). There is no server runtime: `next build` writes the whole site to `out/`, and `wrangler.jsonc` points the Worker's `assets.directory` at it.

```jsonc
"assets": {
  "directory": "out",
  "not_found_handling": "404-page"
}
```

`not_found_handling: "404-page"` makes unmatched paths serve the export's pre-rendered `out/404.html` (the branded not-found page) instead of a blank 404 body.

## First deploy

```bash
bun run deploy   # next build && wrangler deploy
```

`wrangler deploy` prompts a browser login the first time (`wrangler login`) and provisions the Worker under the `name` in `wrangler.jsonc`. The site is then live at `https://<name>.<your-subdomain>.workers.dev`.

Dry-run the upload without publishing:

```bash
wrangler deploy --dry-run
```

## Custom domain

No Terraform / IaC — bind the domain with Wrangler or the dashboard:

- **Wrangler:** add the route to `wrangler.jsonc`, then `wrangler deploy`.

  ```jsonc
  "routes": [
    { "pattern": "example.com", "custom_domain": true }
  ]
  ```

  The zone must already exist in your Cloudflare account; Cloudflare issues and renews the TLS certificate automatically.

- **Dashboard:** Workers & Pages → your Worker → Settings → Domains & Routes → Add → Custom Domain.

DNS for the zone (nameservers, apex/`www` records) is managed in the Cloudflare dashboard — a static scaffolder does not provision it.
